Quick Reference 

1. Create a Git repository in the current folder:
	$ git init 

2. View the status of each file in a repository:
	$ git status

3. Stage a file for the next commit:
	$ git add <file> 

4. Commit the staged files with a descriptive message:
	$ git commit

5. View a repositoryâ€™s commit history:
	$ git log

6. Define the author name to be used in all repositories:
	$ git config --global user.name "<name>"

7. Define the author email to be used in all repositories:
	$ git config --global user.email <email>

